# Example .htpasswd file
# This file should be placed OUTSIDE the web root for security
# 
# To generate this file, use one of these methods:
#
# Method 1: Using htpasswd command (Apache)
#   htpasswd -c .htpasswd cyril
#   (Enter password when prompted: cyril)
#
# Method 2: Using online generator
#   Visit: https://hostingcanada.org/htpasswd-generator/
#   Username: cyril
#   Password: cyril
#   Copy the generated line
#
# Method 3: Using Python
#   python -c "import bcrypt; print('cyril:' + bcrypt.hashpw('cyril'.encode(), bcrypt.gensalt()).decode())"
#
# Method 4: Using htpasswd from Apache (if installed)
#   htpasswd -nb cyril cyril
#
# The file should contain a line like:
# cyril:$apr1$randomstring$hashedpassword
#
# IMPORTANT: 
# - Place this file OUTSIDE the web root (e.g., /home/user/.htpasswd)
# - Update the path in .htaccess: AuthUserFile /home/user/.htpasswd
# - Set proper permissions: chmod 644 .htpasswd
# - Never commit the actual .htpasswd file to git!
